The last unimplemented entry of the canonical-form library
(visual-psychology.md §3.5): a WHOLE ＝ its parts STACKED to the same
height, so the areas carry the identity (資産＝負債＋純資産). Closes the
gap where 'formula' would render an identity as 額装 (equal boxes joined
by ＋ — the symbol-erasure test fails).

- diagrams.js: identityLayout (single source) + CAPS.identity [2,4].
  Proportional heights ONLY with all-numeric parts (all-or-none — the
  engine never invents proportions); else equal split.
- generate.js: slideIdentity builder (house emphasis on one part;
  waterfall-style value fmt; 単位 note bottom-left) + registry.
- geometry.js: whole + every part label baked + height-gated per box.
- design-lint: CAPACITY (n, negative parts -> waterfall誘導, mixed
  values WARN), EMPHASIS_SLOTS, DIAGRAM_PATTERNS, struct words 恒等式/構成.
- schema: pattern enum + content contract.
- docs: diagram-recipes recipe (Verified 2026-07-08), deck-strategy
  capacities, visual-psychology §3.5 machine-face note, READMEs 24->25.
- tests: torture-09-identity-abuse (CAPACITY x3, all-or-none WARN,
  3% slice OVERFLOW; engine must not throw).

Verified: concept form splits equally and closes the identity (stack
bottom = whole bottom, 0.01in); proportional form renders exactly
0.298/0.383/0.318; run-gate PASS across all 6 themes.
